                <h1>Artic Tern Sensor</h1><br>
                <h3><p>AI-Powered Arctic Tern:</h3> Equipped with advanced artificial intelligence to autonomously navigate and collect data.</p><br>   
                <h3><p>High-Resolution Image Capture:</h3> Equipped with a high-resolution camera to capture detailed images of glaciers, icebergs, and surrounding landscapes. </p><br>
                <h3><p>Environmental Sensors:</h3> Includes sensors for measuring wind speed, temperature, and direction, providing valuable insights into local weather conditions.</p><br>
                <h3><p>Data Collection:</h3> The Arctic Tern sensor is programmed to fly over designated areas of glaciers and capture images at regular intervals.
                    Environmental data is collected simultaneously with the images, providing a comprehensive dataset for analysis.
                    Collected data is stored in the sensor's internal memory and transmitted to a ground station via wireless communication.</p><br>
