            <div class="content">
                <h2>Penguin Sensor</h2><br>
                <h3><p>AI-Powered Penguin:</h3> A robotic penguin equipped with advanced AI for autonomous navigation and data collection.</p>  
                <h3>Camera for Visual Monitoring:</h3> Equipped with a high-resolution underwater camera to capture detailed images of the glacial lake bed, ice formations, and potential dam structures.</p><br>
                <!-- <h3>Data Analysis:</h3> -->
                <h3>Lake Size and Water Level:</h3> The Penguin's camera captures images of the lake's shoreline and water surface, allowing for accurate measurements of changes in size and water level over time.</p>
                <h3>Dam Stability:</h3> The camera can detect changes in the appearance of dams, such as cracks, erosion, or bulging, which may indicate instability.</p>
                <h3></h3>Ice Formation:</h3> The Penguin can monitor the formation and melting of ice in the lake, providing insights into potential changes in water flow and dam pressure.</p>
                <h3><p>Image Processing Techniques:</h3> Advanced image processing algorithms are used to analyze the captured images and extract relevant data, such as changes in pixel intensity, object detection, and feature tracking.</p>
            </div>
